PROBLEM:-

     Compute for the income given the monthly sales.
    -----------------------------------------------------------------
         Monthly Sales                          Income
    -------------------------------         -------------------------
    greater than or equal to $50000          $575 plus 16% of sales
    ---------------------------------       -------------------------
    less than $50000 but greater than        $550 plus 14% of Sales
    or equal to $40000                  
    ---------------------------------       -------------------------
    less than $40000 but greater than        $525 plus 12% of Sales
    or equal to $30000                  
    ---------------------------------       -------------------------
    less than $30000 but greater than        $500 plus 9% of Sales
    or equal to $20000                  
    ---------------------------------       -------------------------
    less than $20000 but greater than        $450 plus 5% of Sales
    or equal to $10000                  
    ---------------------------------       -------------------------
    less than $10000                         $400 plus 3% of Sales
    ---------------------------------       -------------------------

ANALYSIS:-

    INPUT:- Input Monthly Sales from User.

PROCESS:-

    profit=(amount+(sales/percentage*100));
    if sale greather than equal to 50000 then income will be $575 and 16% of sales.
    else if sale greater then $40000 and less than equal to $50000 then income will be $550 and 14% of sales.
    else if sale greater then $30000 and less than equal to $40000 then income will be $525 and 12% of sales.
    else if sale greater then $20000 and less than equal to $30000 then income will be $500 and 9% of sales.
    else if sale greater then $10000 and less than equal to $20000 then income will be $450 and 5% of sales.
    else sale less than $10000 then income will be $400 and 3% of sales.

OUTPUT:-

    Print profit.

